    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.WklldBUUO3oesibI]{UM5 Ch.6: Granades &amp; Explosives} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.a6bTH9RIOA1gwoza]{Grenade}&nbsp; @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.tyqnHVNxWuUF1jDk]{EXP (Explosives)} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.C9Q3Yg0CgOm7Ty1N]{(EXP) Concussion} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.oaLjWnlYGoulu7oy]{Tech Level 1}</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This light explosive uses air pressure as well as shrapnel to disrupt enemy lines. They are often employed as mines and in air bursts to break up dense collections of personnel.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">&nbsp;Targets with 10 hit points or less that fail the saving&nbsp;<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">throw are killed.</span></p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Concussion </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1d6 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Physical </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">5 ft. </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Â½ lb. </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">10 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">No </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Detonator</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Physical<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"></span></h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Grenades and explosives with the physical damage type deal bludgeoning damage unless otherwise stated. Medium or smaller targets that don't save against the Dexterity saving throw are knocked prone by the explosion.</span></p>",
